<div class="mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id="Lower_bound_for_learning_rates">Lower bound for learning rates</h2><span class="mw-editsection"><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href="/w/index.php?title=Backtracking_line_search&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4" title="Edit section: Lower bound for learning rates"><span>edit</span></a><span class="mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>This addresses the question whether there is a systematic way to find a positive number <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \beta (\mathbf {x} ,\mathbf {p} )}">
