  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b87bc96d36d1f4d3c81e942c864b212b2ab50b45" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:2.706ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \alpha _{n}}"></span>.</li></ol>
<p>(In <a href="#CITEREFNocedalWright2000">Nocedal &amp; Wright (2000)</a> one can find a description of an algorithm with 1), 3) and 4) above, which was not tested in deep neural networks before the cited paper.)
</p><p>One can save time further by a hybrid mixture between two-way backtracking and the basic standard gradient descent algorithm. This procedure also has good theoretical guarantee and good test performance. Roughly speaking, we run two-way backtracking a few times, then use the learning rate we get from then unchanged, except if the function value increases. Here is precisely how it is done. One choose in advance a number <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle N}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>N</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle N}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f5e3890c981ae85503089652feb48b191b57aae3" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex; width:2.064ex; height:2.176ex;" alt="{\displaystyle N}"></span>, and a number <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle m\leq N}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>≤<!-- ≤ --></mo>
        <mi>N</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle m\leq N}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/423bd606bcb4b31f49a6cebf6fb7defb6e0ddeef" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex; width:7.202ex; height:2.343ex;" alt="{\displaystyle m\leq N}"></span>.
</p>
<ol><li>Set iteration counter j=0.</li>
<li>At the steps <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle jN+1,\ldots ,jN+m}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo>…<!-- … --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle jN+1,\ldots ,jN+m}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/76b1a86dfd543c45526345bba35eab98988e7e92" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.027ex; width:20.132ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle jN+1,\ldots ,jN+m}"></span>, use Two-way Backtracking.</li>
<li>At each step k in the set <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle jN+m+1,\ldots ,jN+N-1}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>m</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mo>…<!-- … --></mo>
        <mo>,</mo>
        <mi>j</mi>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>N</mi>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mn>1</mn>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle jN+m+1,\ldots ,jN+N-1}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/4059cb199b36c7332dfc2778f5911e9cbbd6886e" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; margin-left: -0.027ex; width:29.039ex; height:2.509ex;" alt="{\displaystyle jN+m+1,\ldots ,jN+N-1}"></span>: Set <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle \alpha =\alpha _{k-2}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>α<!-- α --></mi>
        <mo>=</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>α<!-- α --></mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mn>2</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding="application/x-tex">{\displaystyle \alpha =\alpha _{k-2}}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src="https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/5ee7b3e939096bc309dac7e2a4d919903cf84fa6" class="mwe-math-fallback-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden="true" style="vertical-align: -0.671ex; width:9.263ex; height:2.009ex;" alt="{\displaystyle \alpha =\alpha _{k-2}}"></span>. If <span class="mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class="mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style="display: none;"><math xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext="{\displaystyle f(x_{k-1})-f(x_{k-1}+\alpha p_{k-1})\geq 0}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0">
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
        <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
        <mi>f</mi>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <msub>
          <mi>x</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>k</mi>
            <mo>−<!-- − --></mo>
            <mn>1</mn>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mo>+</mo>
        <mi>α<!-- α --></mi>
        <msub>
          <mi>p</mi>
          <mrow class="MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
